{{short description|River in Mexico}}
[[File:PRESA FRANCISCO ZARCO.jpg|thumb|300px]]

The '''Nazas River''' is a [[river]] located in northern [[Mexico]], in territory of the states of [[Coahuila]] and [[Durango]]. It is part of the [[Endorheic basin|endorheic]] [[Bolsón de Mapimí]]. It is only {{convert|560|km|mi}} long, but irrigates an area of {{convert|71906|sqkm|sqmi}} in the middle of the desert. The Nazas is also nurtured by the San Juan, Ramos, Potreritos, del Oro, Nazas, Santiago, [[Tepehuanes River|Tepehuanes]] and Peñón Blanco rivers. The river starts at the [[Sierra Madre Occidental]]. The aboriginal title for this stream is ''Tlahualilo'', coming from the [[Nahuatl]] words ''tlalli'' meaning \fertile land\" and ''ahualila''

